## Worktree Management

All worktree operations use `git gtr`. See the `worktrees` / `setup-gtr` skills for setup.

| Operation | Command |
|-----------|---------|
| Create feature worktree (from main) | `git gtr new feature/{id}-{slug}` |
| Create phase worktree (from feature branch) | `git gtr new {phase-branch} --from-current` |
| List worktrees | `git gtr list` |
| Remove after merge | `git gtr rm {branch} --delete-branch` |
| Batch cleanup merged | `git gtr clean --merged` |

**Directory convention:** `~/worktrees/<repo-name>/<branch-slug>/`

## Branch Naming

| Branch | Pattern | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| Feature | `feature/{parent-id}-{slug}` | `feature/PARENT-100-user-auth` |
| Phase | `feature/{parent-id}-{slug}/phase-{n}-{slug}` | `feature/PARENT-100-user-auth/phase-1-register` |

Tasks commit directly to the phase branch (no per-task branches).

## Completion Signals

```
Task level:       <completion>TASK:{phase_id}:{task_index}:COMPLETE\n{structured body}</completion>
Phase level:      <completion>PHASE:{phase_id}:COMPLETE\n{structured body}</completion>
Feature level:    <completion>FEATURE:{parent_id}:COMPLETE\n{structured body}</completion>
Standalone level: <completion>STANDALONE:{issue_id}:COMPLETE\n{structured body}</completion>
```

Status values: `COMPLETE`, `BLOCKED`, `FAILED`

Each signal includes a structured body with Summary, Verification, and Files Changed sections.

## PR Strategies

| Strategy | Flag | Default? | Behavior |
|----------|------|----------|----------|
| **Stacked** | `--pr-strategy stacked` | Yes | Phase PRs chain: phase-2 → phase-1 → feature |
| **Feature branch** | `--pr-strategy feature` | No | All phase PRs → feature branch directly |

See [references/pr-strategies.md](references/pr-strategies.md) for details.

