## Remember

- **Two modes:** PM mode (default, Linear as source of truth) or local mode (`--local`, state.yaml as source of truth)
- **Local mode:** Read tasks from config.yaml, track progress in state.yaml, sync only phase status to Linear
- **PM mode:** Query PM to resume, no local state files
- **Stacked PRs default** — `--pr-strategy feature` for flat structure
- **Team default, sequential fallback** — auto-detect based on env, task count, mode
- **gtr for worktrees** — never raw `git worktree` commands
- **Code review gate per phase** — reviewer validates before PR creation
- **One commit per task** — Tier 3 skills handle commits
- **Vertical slices** — each phase delivers demoable end-to-end functionality
- **Pattern accumulation** — pass learnings from earlier phases to later ones
- **Sync PM at every transition** — In Progress, In Review, Done (phase-level only in local mode)
- **Completion signals** — structured `<completion>FEATURE:` / `<completion>STANDALONE:` for conductor detection
- **Beads events** — optional audit trail in local mode, fire-and-forget
